 transparent_bg="transparent-bg-0" parallax="" bgtype="image" bgfixed="no" css=".vc_custom_1431039787425{padding-bottom: 30px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>WHAT IS <span style="color: #ff0000;">ALLEY ART AMAZIN’</span>?</h2>\n<p><span style="color: #2a2a2a;">Founded in 2011, Alley Art Amazin’ is a grassroots organization in Old Town Lafayette. We are ordinary people who love art, doing extraordinary work to improve the world we live in, specifically our community, Lafayette, Colorado.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #2a2a2a;">This great program was started by Old Town residents John Weise and Marissa Saints. When Marissa’s garage was tagged with graffiti, instead of merely covering it up, she decided to turn it into a mural. With John’s enthusiasm to spread the word about his love for Lafayette, the program was born.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #2a2a2a;">Since it’s conception, Alley Art Amazin’ has grown to include more than 50 murals and art pieces scattered about Old Town’s alleyways. As we are entering our fifth season, Alley Art Amazin’ art directors are gearing up to bring their talent and paint brushes to help residents and business paint new ‘canvases’.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #2a2a2a;">Our goal is to engage the community to tap into their inner creativity, working with professional artists to give life and art to Lafayette’s alleyways and side streets. We aim to continue to give Old Town Lafayette colorful and inviting galleries of public art, just a walk or bike ride away . We also promote the curbing of unwanted tagging and graffiti. By beautifying the alleyways, sheds, outbuildings and fences of Old Town Lafayette, the Alley Art Amazin’ program inspires creativity, encourages exploration and bonds our unique community.</span>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_widget_sidebar sidebar_id="post-widget"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row box_padding="pad-top-bottom-80" theme_color="darkness" 